                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111348">East Ham</placeName>, <placeName key="place_113978">Wennington</placeName>, <placeName key="place_113979">Great Fanton Hall alias Fan
                        Hall</placeName>, <placeName key="place_111687">Morden</placeName>, <placeName key="place_113980">Aldenham</placeName>, <placeName key="place_113983">Holwell</placeName>, <placeName key="place_111424">Datchworth</placeName>, <placeName key="place_1083582">Watton-at-Stone</placeName>, <placeName key="place_113984">Chollington</placeName>, <placeName key="place_113981">Bleccenham
                        (lost)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_113982">Lothereslege
                        (lost)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_113346">Staines</placeName>, <placeName key="place_113985">Teddington</placeName>, <placeName key="place_113986">Halliford</placeName>, <placeName key="place_113987">Feltham</placeName>, <placeName key="place_113988">Ashford</placeName>. King Edgar to Westminster Abbey [St Peter's, Thorney], confirmation,
                        reciting a bull of Pope John [Pope John XIII], of liberties and of land at
                        Ham (in East Ham), Wennington, Essex; Morden, Surrey; Fanton (Hall) in North
                        Benfleet, Essex; Aldenham, Herts.; Bleccenham and Lothereslege (both lost,
                        in Hendon), Middx; Holwell, Datchworth and Watton-at-Stone, Herts.;
                        Chollington in Eastbourne, Sussex; Staines, with Teddington, Halliford,
                        Feltham and Ashford, Middx.  <origDate when="0969">969, Id. Maii (= May 15)</origDate>
                     </p>
